article.headline: Baylor 74, Nebraska 70
article.story: WACO, Texas -- LaceDarius Dunn scored 20 of his 24 points after halftime to help Baylor beat Nebraska 74-70 on Wednesday night. Dunn scored Baylor's first seven points after halftime, capping it with a 3-pointer that broke a 36-all tie and put the Bears (16-7, 6-4 Big 12) ahead to stay. Right after that, Baylor's A.J. Walton had a steal and a breakaway layup. Nebraska (15-8, 3-6) failed to take advantage of a turnover by Dunn in the final minute. The Bears converted when Dunn made an over-the-shoulder layup for a 71-67 lead. Dunn hit two more free throws with 16 seconds left after Anthony Jones blocked a long 3-point attempt by Nebraska's Toney McCray. McCray led the Cornhuskers with 23 points and Lance Jeter had 13. Quincy Acy added 15 points and seven rebounds for Baylor.
